---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ChapterSummary from '../../components/ChapterSummary.astro';

const chapters = [
  { href: '#setup', label: 'Setup' },
  { href: '#face-down', label: 'Face-down cards' },
  { href: '#traps', label: 'Traps' },
  { href: '#summons', label: 'Special summons' },
  { href: '#timing', label: 'Timing' },
  { href: '#actions', label: 'Cube actions' },
  { href: '#archetypes', label: 'Archetypes' },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Cube rules — YGO × MTG"
  description="Rules unique to the YGO × MTG cube, including face-down cards, Traps, Extra Deck summons, timing, and archetype mechanics."
  theme="home"
>
  <article class="page-shell info-page">
    <header>
      <p>YGO × MTG</p>
      <h1>Cube rules</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Normal Magic rules apply unless this page says otherwise. Card text uses
        Yu-Gi-Oh! timing and identity inside Magic’s stack, zones, combat, and
        turn structure.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="info-layout">
      <div class="info-content">
        <section id="setup">
          <h2>Setup and mulligan</h2>
          <p>
            This is a closed, high-power cube. Extra Deck cards—Fusion, Synchro,
            Xyz, and Link Creatures—start in the Sideboard, which represents the
            Extra Deck. Ritual Creatures remain in the Main Deck.
          </p>
          <h3>Cube mulligan</h3>
          <ol>
            <li>
              Once before the game, choose any number of cards in your opening
              hand.
            </li>
            <li>Put those cards on the bottom of your Deck in any order.</li>
            <li>Draw the same number of cards. Do not shuffle.</li>
          </ol>
        </section>

        <section id="face-down">
          <h2>Face-down creatures</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Any creature may be cast face down for its normal cost.</li>
            <li>
              Face down, it has no name, color, type, ability, power, or
              toughness.
            </li>
            <li>
              It cannot be Flipped during the turn it enters. From the next
              turn, its controller may Flip it at sorcery speed.
            </li>
            <li>
              A face-down creature may be Fusion or Ritual material, but not
              Synchro or Xyz material.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Flip</strong> triggers when the creature turns face up.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="traps">
          <h2>Trap cards</h2>
          <p>
            Trap is a supertype, such as <code>Trap Instant</code> or
            <code>Trap Enchantment</code>. A Trap cannot normally be cast from
            hand.
          </p>
          <ol>
            <li>
              <strong>Set</strong> it face down on the field as a special action.
              Setting does not use the stack, pay its casting cost, or count as a
              cast.
            </li>
            <li>
              While face down, it is a nameless, colorless, typeless nonland,
              noncreature permanent with no abilities or mana value.
            </li>
            <li>
              Starting on the following turn, turn it face up and cast it from
              the field at instant speed, paying normal costs. This uses the
              stack and counts as a cast from the field.
            </li>
            <li>
              Trap Instants and Sorceries go to Grave after resolving. Trap
              permanents enter face up. Explicit same-turn permission removes
              only the one-turn wait.
            </li>
          </ol>
        </section>

        <section id="summons">
          <h2>Special summons and the Extra Deck</h2>
          <p>
            Fusion, Synchro, Xyz, Link, and Ritual Creatures must be properly
            summoned by their named method before another effect can cast or put
            them onto the field. “Ignoring the restrictions of Summon” allows
            the immediate move, but does not make it a proper summon for later
            returns.
          </p>
          <dl class="rule-glossary">
            <div>
              <dt>Ritual Summon</dt><dd>
                Use listed materials; their total MV equals the Ritual
                Creature’s MV unless the card allows more.
              </dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Fusion Summon</dt><dd>
                Move a Fusion Creature from Sideboard to field using its listed
                materials and zones.
              </dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Synchro Summon</dt><dd>
                Use 1 Tuner plus listed non-Tuners whose total MV equals the
                Synchro Creature’s MV.
              </dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Xyz Summon</dt><dd>
                Use listed same-MV creatures, placing them under the Xyz
                Creature as materials. <strong>Detach X</strong> sends X materials
                to Grave.
              </dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Link Summon</dt><dd>
                Use the number and kind of materials on the card. Link level
                appears in its type line.
              </dd>
            </div>
          </dl>
        </section>

        <section id="timing">
          <h2>Abilities, timing, and limits</h2>
          <p>
            Numbered abilities identify type, timing, and frequency. Costs and
            targets appear before a semicolon; resolution follows it. Targeting
            is never itself a cost.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Static:</strong> always active.</li>
            <li>
              <strong>Activated Ritual:</strong> activate at sorcery speed.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Activated Flash:</strong> activate at instant speed.
            </li>
            <li><strong>Triggered:</strong> triggers from its named event.</li>
            <li><strong>Soft:</strong> once per turn for that object.</li>
            <li>
              <strong>Hard:</strong> once per turn across cards with that name.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Hard Linked:</strong> use only one linked ability of that named
              card each turn.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <h3>Common events</h3>
          <p>
            <strong>On Cast</strong> means your spells; Opponent and Any change the
            controller scope. <strong>On Send Grave</strong> includes every route
            to Grave; <strong>On Send Grave by Effect</strong> excludes costs and
            rules actions. <strong>On Fusion Summon</strong> and
            <strong>On Link Summon</strong>
            require the proper named summon, not an effect that merely puts the card
            onto the field. Other event labels—On Destroy, On Leave Field, On Upkeep,
            On End Step, On Blocked, On Block or Blocked, and On Opponent Summon—use
            their literal Magic event.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="actions">
          <h2>Cube action glossary</h2>
          <dl class="rule-glossary">
            <div>
              <dt>Summon</dt><dd>
                Put the indicated card onto the field without casting or paying
                its mana cost.
              </dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Hand Summon</dt><dd>
                Summon the indicated creature from hand.
              </dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Reanimate</dt><dd>
                Return the targeted card from Grave to field.
              </dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Salvage</dt><dd>
                Return the indicated card from Grave to hand.
              </dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Reclaim</dt><dd>
                Return the indicated card from exile to hand.
              </dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Release</dt><dd>
                Put the indicated exiled card onto the field.
              </dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Mill N</dt><dd>
                Send N cards from the top of your Deck to Grave.
              </dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Attach</dt><dd>
                Attach the indicated card to an Xyz Creature as material.
              </dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Bounce</dt><dd>
                Return the indicated permanent to its owner’s hand.
              </dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Negate</dt><dd>
                Counter a spell or ability; for a permanent, remove its
                abilities and counter its abilities on the stack.
              </dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Negate &amp; Destroy</dt><dd>
                Negate, then destroy the source when it is in field, hand, Deck,
                or Sideboard.
              </dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Effect Indestructible</dt><dd>
                Cannot be destroyed by spells or abilities; combat and
                non-effect rules may still destroy it.
              </dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Bounded X</dt><dd>
                Choose up to X creatures linked to a bounder. Their bonus lasts
                only while that bounder remains on field.
              </dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Exile from Grave</dt><dd>
                Activate in Grave and exile this card as a cost.
              </dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Slow Blink X Any Creature</dt><dd>
                Target 0–X creatures; exile them until next end step, then
                return them under their owners’ control.
              </dd>
            </div>
          </dl>
          <p>
            Unqualified hand, Deck, Grave, and exile mean your corresponding
            zone. The battlefield is shared. <strong>Alternative Cost</strong>
            replaces a normal casting cost only as printed.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="archetypes">
          <h2>Archetype-specific rules</h2>
          <h3>Burning Abyss</h3>
          <p>
            <strong>Descent:</strong> at sorcery speed, if you have not Summoned a
            “Burning Abyss” creature this turn, Summon this card from hand.
            <strong>Abyssal Curse:</strong> if you control another creature without
            “Burning Abyss” in its name, destroy this creature. Abyssal Curse applies
            to non-Ritual Main Deck Burning Abyss creatures.
          </p>
          <h3>Shaddoll</h3>
          <p>
            <strong>Shaddoll Recovery:</strong> On Send Grave, Salvage 1 non-creature
            “Shaddoll”. On Send Grave by Effect remains a separate event.
          </p>
          <h3>Nekroz</h3>
          <p>
            Nekroz Ritual Creatures can be cast only through Ritual Summon.
            Unless a card says otherwise, each effect of a named Nekroz creature
            is usable once per turn. <strong>Nekroz Recovery:</strong> if you control
            no creatures, exile this card and 1 other “Nekroz” from Grave to Search
            1 non-creature Ritual Summon “Nekroz”.
          </p>
          <h3>Spellbook</h3>
          <p>
            <strong>Spell Affinity</strong> appears only on eligible Spellbook Sorceries.
            If you control 1 “Spellbook” creature, you may cast that spell without
            paying its mana cost. Use this alternative cost only once each turn. Cards
            without the printed keyword do not gain it.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>

      <ChapterSummary items={chapters} />
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
